        <p class="lead">Germantown is a market where your competitors in Gaithersburg and Rockville have had proper schema and 90+ PageSpeed for years while many Germantown businesses remain on outdated Wix sites - and are losing search visibility to those competitors as a result. The contractors, medical practices, and restaurants ranking in the Local Pack here are on optimized WordPress. A Wix or GoDaddy site built in 2019 is not competing on the same field, and in a diverse community where multilingual search patterns add another ranking layer, that gap shows up as lost leads every single week.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="lp-compare-cols">

        <div class="lp-compare-col lp-compare-col-wp">
          <div class="lp-compare-col-head">
            <span class="lp-compare-badge lp-compare-badge-wp mono-xs">Custom WordPress</span>
            <p class="lp-compare-col-sub">Built from scratch, owned by you</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="lp-compare-list">
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-good">You own the code outright - no platform can raise prices or shut you down</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-good">PageSpeed 90+ is achievable with correct setup - Core Web Vitals consistently pass</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-good">Full JSON-LD schema support for Local Pack and rich results</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-good">Any plugin, any integration, any custom function - no artificial limits</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-good">No monthly platform fee after launch - only hosting and optional care plan</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-neutral">Significant changes require a developer - not a drag-and-drop interface</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="lp-compare-col lp-compare-col-diy">
          <div class="lp-compare-col-head">
            <span class="lp-compare-badge lp-compare-badge-diy mono-xs">Wix / Squarespace / GoDaddy</span>
            <p class="lp-compare-col-sub">Rented platform, shared infrastructure</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="lp-compare-list">
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-neutral">Fast to get started - drag and drop, no developer needed initially</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-bad">PageSpeed typically 50-70 - Core Web Vitals frequently fail on mobile</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-bad">Limited schema markup - Local Pack ranking is harder without full JSON-LD control</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-bad">You rent the site - the platform controls your data, your URL structure, your export options</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-bad">Monthly fees scale with traffic, ecommerce features, and storage</li>
            <li class="lp-ci lp-ci-bad">Migrating away costs time and risks ranking loss without a proper redirect strategy</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

      </div>

      <p class="lp-compare-note">
        Wix and Squarespace are workable starting points for a business that isn't competing on Google. For a Germantown contractor competing for "germantown contractor" against Gaithersburg and Rockville businesses that've had proper HomeAndConstructionBusiness schema and 90+ PageSpeed for three years, or a Middlebrook Road medical practice competing against offices with Physician schema and multilingual hreflang since 2022 - the platform gap isn't hypothetical. It shows up as position 8 instead of position 2, and in an upcounty Montgomery County market where well-optimized competitors are already ranking, that position difference is the difference between a full calendar and chasing leads.
